    <p class="ex">Sebaba. We have two "divs" that have the class "row" (because we want two rows) and in each row we create three divs with the class "column" and inside those we placed our headings and images. Proper indenting is really important here to keep our HTML readable.</p>

    <h5>The CSS</h5>
    <p>Now we want all 3 of our columns to equally cover the width of the page. For that, we'll use a percentage width so that we know no matter how big the screen is, one column will still cover 1/3 of the page. And since we're balsy, let's use float (also, we'll be floating ALL of the "column" class' siblings, which are just columns). Add the following:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#9b703f">.column</span> {
  <span style="color:#c5af75">float</span>: <span style="color:#f9ee98">left</span>;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">width</span>: <span style="color:#dd7b3b">33.3<span style="color:#e28964">%</span></span>;
}
</pre>

    <p>Now for our images, let's set their width to 100% so that we know they will always fill the column, but not more. Add the following CSS:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#9b703f">.food</span> <span style="color:#cda869">img</span> {
